G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: Massachusetts law, specifically G.L. c. 186, § 14, provides that a landlord who interferes with a tenant’s quiet enjoyment of leased premises shall be liable for damages.

G.L. c. 218, \u00a7 19.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this matter pursuant to G.L. c. 218, § 19 because the damages sought are within the jurisdictional limit of the Boston Municipal Court.

G.L. c. 223, \u00a7\u00a7 2 and 8.proposition: Venue is proper in the Jamaica Plain Division of the Boston Municipal Court pursuant to G.L. c. 223, §§ 2 and 8 because the leased premises giving rise to this claim are located in Jamaica Plain.
